    ~3.23% coverage (all 205 edges created_by='manual'). Flip them to default-ON with
    an opt-out env each (isOptInEnabled -> isFeatureEnabled):
    - SPECKIT_POST_INSERT_ENRICHMENT_ENABLED (causal links + entities + summaries + graph lifecycle)
    - SPECKIT_RECONSOLIDATION_ENABLED (save-time FSRS stability reconsolidation)
    - SPECKIT_QUALITY_AUTO_FIX (trigger phrases, char-budget trim, anchor normalize)
    
    Run the enrichment bundle asynchronously (default) so saves stay fast: a
    setImmediate after the commit runs runPostInsertEnrichment in the background and
    records the result; the save returns immediately with enrichmentStatus deferred
    (reason async-background). Crash safety reuses the existing markEnrichmentPending
    (written in the commit tx) + replay/backfill repair. New
    SPECKIT_POST_INSERT_ENRICHMENT_SYNC=true forces synchronous enrichment.
    
    Verified live: real saves now enrich by default — causal edges gained 4
    created_by='entity_linker' rows (was 100% manual); recent rows show
    post_insert_enrichment_status=complete with extracted entities.
    
    Docs (ENV_REFERENCE.md + feature_catalog.md) updated to default-on + async + the
    new SYNC flag. Spec packet 026/.../017 validates --strict 0/0. Two pre-existing
    handler-memory-index scan-fixture failures are unrelated (red on HEAD).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

